WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.880 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:27.804 align:middle line:10%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:27.804 --> 00:00:30.220 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: Perhaps the
deepest area of exploration

00:00:30.220 --> 00:00:32.800 align:middle line:10%
that any of us will undertake
is the journey into connection

00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:34.630 align:middle line:10%
with our own soul force.

00:00:34.630 --> 00:00:37.700 align:middle line:84%
Known by many names, there
is no journey more rewarding,

00:00:37.700 --> 00:00:41.500 align:middle line:84%
nor more convoluted, than
coming to know thyself.

00:00:41.500 --> 00:00:44.200 align:middle line:84%
But in doing so, we
become a free species,

00:00:44.200 --> 00:00:46.600 align:middle line:84%
unable to be controlled
by outside forces

00:00:46.600 --> 00:00:49.760 align:middle line:90%
and alive with possibility.

00:00:49.760 --> 00:00:52.710 align:middle line:90%
Carrie, this is your area.

00:00:52.710 --> 00:00:54.640 align:middle line:84%
Carrie L'Esperance
is with us today.

00:00:54.640 --> 00:00:57.790 align:middle line:84%
And when I was reading
your book, just

00:00:57.790 --> 00:01:01.810 align:middle line:84%
from the very first pages,
I saw this incredibly mature

00:01:01.810 --> 00:01:06.370 align:middle line:84%
understanding of what's needed
today, and also of the notion

00:01:06.370 --> 00:01:08.740 align:middle line:84%
of what it takes to begin
connecting with soul,

00:01:08.740 --> 00:01:10.600 align:middle line:90%
which is my passion as well.

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:12.700 align:middle line:84%
So I have almost
every ear dog paged,

00:01:12.700 --> 00:01:15.240 align:middle line:84%
because we're on the
same page, literally.

00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:17.440 align:middle line:84%
>>CARRIE L'ESPERANCE:
Wonderful so happy to hear it.

00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:21.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: First of all, I want
to say something that is just

00:01:21.130 --> 00:01:22.250 align:middle line:90%
coming up more and more.

00:01:22.250 --> 00:01:24.820 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not taking a
swipe at the male species,

00:01:24.820 --> 00:01:29.020 align:middle line:84%
but maybe the more masculine way
of functioning in the world--

00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:32.179 align:middle line:84%
that most of the books, most
of the religions, almost

00:01:32.179 --> 00:01:33.970 align:middle line:84%
everything that's
perpetuated in the world,

00:01:33.970 --> 00:01:38.710 align:middle line:84%
is through the male mind,
often generally men.

00:01:38.710 --> 00:01:42.160 align:middle line:84%
The reality is that while
the left side of the brain

00:01:42.160 --> 00:01:44.500 align:middle line:84%
is pretty good at putting
function together,

00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:49.480 align:middle line:84%
structure together,
my personal experience

00:01:49.480 --> 00:01:53.200 align:middle line:84%
is that the people who
experience these realities more

00:01:53.200 --> 00:01:58.600 align:middle line:84%
naturally are women, or the
feminine aspect of being.

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:01.630 align:middle line:84%
What do you have say about that,
before we even get rolling?

00:02:01.630 --> 00:02:03.880 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: You
know, I've heard this.

00:02:03.880 --> 00:02:07.360 align:middle line:10%
But the truth is, what
you're talking about

00:02:07.360 --> 00:02:09.520 align:middle line:10%
is basically intuition.

00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:12.230 align:middle line:10%
And everyone has intuition.

00:02:12.230 --> 00:02:16.000 align:middle line:10%
But it's like a muscle
that has to be exercised.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.390 align:middle line:84%
So men are very trained
to think linearly.

00:02:20.390 --> 00:02:24.640 align:middle line:90%


00:02:24.640 --> 00:02:28.060 align:middle line:84%
Actually, scientifically
it's proven that women do

00:02:28.060 --> 00:02:31.780 align:middle line:84%
have what's called
a thicker corpus

00:02:31.780 --> 00:02:34.630 align:middle line:84%
callosum in the brain
that connects the right

00:02:34.630 --> 00:02:37.900 align:middle line:84%
and left hemispheres
of the brain.

00:02:37.900 --> 00:02:44.170 align:middle line:84%
And that enables women to more
easily bounce back and forth

00:02:44.170 --> 00:02:49.540 align:middle line:84%
between linear thinking and
more non-linear thinking.

00:02:49.540 --> 00:02:52.990 align:middle line:84%
So they say, yes, women
have this-- more naturally

00:02:52.990 --> 00:02:54.125 align:middle line:90%
they have it.

00:02:54.125 --> 00:02:56.250 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And multitasking
falls within that, where

00:02:56.250 --> 00:02:57.541 align:middle line:90%
you're flipping back and forth.

00:02:57.541 --> 00:02:58.760 align:middle line:90%
Oh gosh, I have to do that.

00:02:58.760 --> 00:03:00.140 align:middle line:90%
I'm still doing that.

00:03:00.140 --> 00:03:05.320 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: But honestly,
my feeling about it is that

00:03:05.320 --> 00:03:10.760 align:middle line:84%
if-- women have been using this
because they've had to use it--

00:03:10.760 --> 00:03:11.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Indeed.

00:03:11.560 --> 00:03:12.580 align:middle line:90%
>>L'ESPERANCE: --to survive--

00:03:12.580 --> 00:03:13.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:03:13.150 --> 00:03:14.080 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE:
--in a man's world.

00:03:14.080 --> 00:03:15.040 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:18.310 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: The body,
on an evolutionary scale,

00:03:18.310 --> 00:03:22.990 align:middle line:84%
would begin to develop
more in that direction.

00:03:22.990 --> 00:03:26.262 align:middle line:84%
It's not necessarily that men
don't have the ability to--

00:03:26.262 --> 00:03:27.220 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You're right.

00:03:27.220 --> 00:03:28.690 align:middle line:90%
We all have it.

00:03:28.690 --> 00:03:33.100 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: --let's say,
grow a thicker corpus callosum.

00:03:33.100 --> 00:03:36.940 align:middle line:84%
And I think women have evolved
this way because they've

00:03:36.940 --> 00:03:38.410 align:middle line:90%
been allowed to.

00:03:38.410 --> 00:03:39.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree.

00:03:39.210 --> 00:03:41.168 align:middle line:84%
And because this has been
societal conditioning

00:03:41.168 --> 00:03:44.290 align:middle line:84%
for a few thousand
years, on both sides.

00:03:44.290 --> 00:03:48.520 align:middle line:84%
But what I find is--
and it's interesting.

00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:51.850 align:middle line:84%
And you're very
good at expression--

00:03:51.850 --> 00:03:53.770 align:middle line:84%
personal expression--
and putting language

00:03:53.770 --> 00:03:55.750 align:middle line:90%
to the non-physical reality.

00:03:55.750 --> 00:03:57.820 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of times
the people that

00:03:57.820 --> 00:04:00.580 align:middle line:84%
do experience it
so deeply, and who

00:04:00.580 --> 00:04:03.520 align:middle line:84%
I can have these
conversations with,

00:04:03.520 --> 00:04:09.039 align:middle line:84%
can't always verbalize it to the
same degree, in a linear sense.

00:04:09.039 --> 00:04:11.080 align:middle line:84%
So most of the people I
interview on these topics

00:04:11.080 --> 00:04:12.340 align:middle line:90%
are men, is what I'm saying.

00:04:12.340 --> 00:04:12.820 align:middle line:90%
>>L'ESPERANCE: OK.

00:04:12.820 --> 00:04:13.903 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: For that reason.

00:04:13.903 --> 00:04:16.420 align:middle line:84%
Because the facility
to experience it

00:04:16.420 --> 00:04:22.350 align:middle line:84%
can't exactly be laid into words
the way that we would prefer,

00:04:22.350 --> 00:04:23.150 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:04:23.150 --> 00:04:23.560 align:middle line:90%
>>L'ESPERANCE: Yes, I think--

00:04:23.560 --> 00:04:25.000 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you've done
a pretty darn good job.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:27.291 align:middle line:84%
I'm just pointing this out,
because it's a conversation

00:04:27.291 --> 00:04:28.600 align:middle line:90%
we need to get at.

00:04:28.600 --> 00:04:30.807 align:middle line:84%
But it's a conversation
about non-physical realms,

00:04:30.807 --> 00:04:32.140 align:middle line:90%
and connecting, and the need to.

00:04:32.140 --> 00:04:33.610 align:middle line:90%
And you've done a beautiful job.

00:04:33.610 --> 00:04:35.800 align:middle line:84%
So let's take a journey
back into your own life.

00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:40.240 align:middle line:84%
And when did you become aware
that this deep connection was

00:04:40.240 --> 00:04:44.920 align:middle line:84%
not only available, but
was absolutely necessary?

00:04:44.920 --> 00:04:47.810 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: From
the time I was a child,

00:04:47.810 --> 00:04:51.450 align:middle line:84%
I've had this deep
connection with my soul.

00:04:51.450 --> 00:04:55.010 align:middle line:84%
From the time I
was very young, I

00:04:55.010 --> 00:04:58.790 align:middle line:84%
felt like I was much
older than my body.

00:04:58.790 --> 00:05:05.300 align:middle line:84%
And I think that if we
recognize that every soul has

00:05:05.300 --> 00:05:07.880 align:middle line:84%
a fingerprint, a unique
fingerprint-- just

00:05:07.880 --> 00:05:10.070 align:middle line:84%
like our fingers have
unique fingerprints,

00:05:10.070 --> 00:05:12.800 align:middle line:84%
each soul has a
unique fingerprint.

00:05:12.800 --> 00:05:16.190 align:middle line:84%
And there are definitely
different levels of souls.

00:05:16.190 --> 00:05:17.520 align:middle line:90%
Some are beginner souls.

00:05:17.520 --> 00:05:18.540 align:middle line:90%
Some are advanced.

00:05:18.540 --> 00:05:20.910 align:middle line:90%
And some are old souls.

00:05:20.910 --> 00:05:24.440 align:middle line:84%
And so the journey
in the physical body

00:05:24.440 --> 00:05:27.540 align:middle line:90%
is really exactly what it is.

00:05:27.540 --> 00:05:28.350 align:middle line:90%
It's a journey.

00:05:28.350 --> 00:05:34.430 align:middle line:84%
And every soul comes in to a
physical, third dimensional

00:05:34.430 --> 00:05:37.940 align:middle line:84%
reality, with a soul
contract, with something

00:05:37.940 --> 00:05:41.540 align:middle line:84%
that you're supposed
to work out.

00:05:41.540 --> 00:05:47.220 align:middle line:84%
And the soul knows
what that work is.

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:50.870 align:middle line:84%
That's why it's so important
to connect with the soul.

00:05:50.870 --> 00:05:53.880 align:middle line:84%
Because third dimensional
physical reality

00:05:53.880 --> 00:05:56.350 align:middle line:90%
is designed for distraction.

00:05:56.350 --> 00:06:01.250 align:middle line:84%
There's so many ways people
can get off track in life.

00:06:01.250 --> 00:06:06.080 align:middle line:84%
And it's almost as
though it's on purpose.

00:06:06.080 --> 00:06:09.900 align:middle line:84%
It's almost as though,
from the time we're young,

00:06:09.900 --> 00:06:12.800 align:middle line:84%
we aren't taught about
the deeper realities,

00:06:12.800 --> 00:06:14.730 align:middle line:84%
although we know
that they're there,

00:06:14.730 --> 00:06:17.810 align:middle line:90%
and we know that they exist.

00:06:17.810 --> 00:06:21.050 align:middle line:84%
But we aren't really
supported in learning

00:06:21.050 --> 00:06:25.250 align:middle line:90%
about personal power.

00:06:25.250 --> 00:06:27.500 align:middle line:84%
And I really believe
that if children

00:06:27.500 --> 00:06:32.570 align:middle line:84%
were taught, from a very young
age, about who they really are

00:06:32.570 --> 00:06:34.910 align:middle line:84%
and what they really
are capable of,

00:06:34.910 --> 00:06:37.650 align:middle line:84%
it would be a very
different world.

00:06:37.650 --> 00:06:40.770 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And also, if they
were taught to simply live

00:06:40.770 --> 00:06:42.630 align:middle line:90%
in their own true way--

00:06:42.630 --> 00:06:43.430 align:middle line:90%
>>L'ESPERANCE: Yes.

00:06:43.430 --> 00:06:45.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --so that
the parents could even

00:06:45.180 --> 00:06:46.890 align:middle line:84%
help in the process
of observation,

00:06:46.890 --> 00:06:49.530 align:middle line:84%
to see where they're
naturally gravitating,

00:06:49.530 --> 00:06:53.160 align:middle line:84%
then the parents could even
help reinforce these paths

00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:54.780 align:middle line:90%
of discovery they're on.

00:06:54.780 --> 00:06:55.680 align:middle line:90%
But we don't do that.

00:06:55.680 --> 00:06:58.200 align:middle line:90%
We have a plan for our children.

00:06:58.200 --> 00:07:00.030 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: Well,
you're a child,

00:07:00.030 --> 00:07:03.320 align:middle line:84%
and you come into the
world, and you're put in,

00:07:03.320 --> 00:07:08.760 align:middle line:84%
let's say-- like
I was-- catechism.

00:07:08.760 --> 00:07:11.960 align:middle line:84%
And you learn that
you're a sinner.

00:07:11.960 --> 00:07:15.980 align:middle line:84%
And you learn that you
are to worship that which

00:07:15.980 --> 00:07:17.520 align:middle line:90%
is outside of yourself.

00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:20.930 align:middle line:84%
You are to seek
what you are looking

00:07:20.930 --> 00:07:24.440 align:middle line:90%
for everywhere but within.

00:07:24.440 --> 00:07:29.400 align:middle line:84%
And for me, I always thought
everybody else was just

00:07:29.400 --> 00:07:30.560 align:middle line:90%
like me.

00:07:30.560 --> 00:07:34.820 align:middle line:84%
Because everything
that I did was

00:07:34.820 --> 00:07:38.120 align:middle line:90%
from that place, deep within.

00:07:38.120 --> 00:07:42.720 align:middle line:84%
And I would see people
getting married at young ages,

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:45.590 align:middle line:84%
or doing all kinds of
things that they had plenty

00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:47.400 align:middle line:84%
of time to do, but
they were pressured

00:07:47.400 --> 00:07:49.530 align:middle line:90%
by cultural conditioning.

00:07:49.530 --> 00:07:50.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:07:50.690 --> 00:07:56.130 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: And I would ask
them, well, ask your higher

00:07:56.130 --> 00:07:56.930 align:middle line:90%
self.

00:07:56.930 --> 00:07:58.020 align:middle line:90%
Go deeper.

00:07:58.020 --> 00:07:59.400 align:middle line:90%
Go deeper within.

00:07:59.400 --> 00:08:05.400 align:middle line:84%
And that's how you know what's
right and what your path is.

00:08:05.400 --> 00:08:07.100 align:middle line:90%
And I've always lived this way.

00:08:07.100 --> 00:08:11.600 align:middle line:84%
And my work in the
world has always

00:08:11.600 --> 00:08:17.490 align:middle line:84%
been in alignment with, I guess,
the old adage, know thyself.

00:08:17.490 --> 00:08:18.290 align:middle line:90%
Know thyself.

00:08:18.290 --> 00:08:20.410 align:middle line:90%
Seek to know thyself.

00:08:20.410 --> 00:08:21.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:08:21.440 --> 00:08:28.430 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: And my path
has been one of observation,

00:08:28.430 --> 00:08:31.890 align:middle line:84%
one of experience,
one of research.

00:08:31.890 --> 00:08:35.039 align:middle line:84%
And the experience,
I have to say,

00:08:35.039 --> 00:08:37.426 align:middle line:90%
is the most powerful teacher.

00:08:37.426 --> 00:08:38.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:08:38.610 --> 00:08:41.299 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: Life
is the master teacher.

00:08:41.299 --> 00:08:45.980 align:middle line:84%
And so for me, I
felt that it was

00:08:45.980 --> 00:08:48.300 align:middle line:84%
very important at
this point in my life

00:08:48.300 --> 00:08:51.600 align:middle line:84%
to write a book
that helped people

00:08:51.600 --> 00:08:55.460 align:middle line:84%
to understand what is really
happening in the world, why

00:08:55.460 --> 00:08:58.580 align:middle line:84%
it's happening, and
what we can do about it.

00:08:58.580 --> 00:09:03.630 align:middle line:84%
It hasn't been an easy path to
understand or to learn about.

00:09:03.630 --> 00:09:06.950 align:middle line:84%
And I also felt like I
was putting myself out

00:09:06.950 --> 00:09:10.350 align:middle line:84%
on the line a bit by adding
certain things to the book.

00:09:10.350 --> 00:09:11.405 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I understand.

00:09:11.405 --> 00:09:12.780 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE:
But I felt that it

00:09:12.780 --> 00:09:15.960 align:middle line:84%
was imperative to
add the things that

00:09:15.960 --> 00:09:19.900 align:middle line:84%
were more difficult for people
to receive and understand

00:09:19.900 --> 00:09:24.390 align:middle line:84%
than not to add them,
because it's a big picture.

00:09:24.390 --> 00:09:28.005 align:middle line:84%
And everything is woven
together, like a tapestry.

00:09:28.005 --> 00:09:33.150 align:middle line:90%


00:09:33.150 --> 00:09:37.590 align:middle line:84%
Anyone who understands life,
and the processes of life,

00:09:37.590 --> 00:09:46.560 align:middle line:84%
can see that it's a
hierarchical, planetary design.

00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:51.090 align:middle line:84%
In other words, the
seed needs the soil.

00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:54.740 align:middle line:90%
The soil needs the rain.

00:09:54.740 --> 00:10:00.710 align:middle line:84%
The plant flowers because of
the sunlight and the nurturing

00:10:00.710 --> 00:10:01.840 align:middle line:90%
nutrients in the soil.

00:10:01.840 --> 00:10:02.640 align:middle line:90%
All these things--

00:10:02.640 --> 00:10:03.972 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Released by the rain.

00:10:03.972 --> 00:10:05.430 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: It's
all reciprocal.

00:10:05.430 --> 00:10:06.800 align:middle line:90%
Life is reciprocal.

00:10:06.800 --> 00:10:12.850 align:middle line:84%
We have to understand
this also about ourselves.

00:10:12.850 --> 00:10:20.350 align:middle line:84%
And we have to get away from
the idea that what we want

00:10:20.350 --> 00:10:23.434 align:middle line:84%
is not necessarily
what our work is.

00:10:23.434 --> 00:10:24.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No,
because we're coming

00:10:24.850 --> 00:10:26.410 align:middle line:90%
from another aspect of being.

00:10:26.410 --> 00:10:27.790 align:middle line:84%
We're usually
coming from what we

00:10:27.790 --> 00:10:29.664 align:middle line:84%
call the conscious mind,
which, of course, is

00:10:29.664 --> 00:10:31.300 align:middle line:84%
the least conscious
part of our mind--

00:10:31.300 --> 00:10:34.840 align:middle line:84%
is our conscious mind, which
also has to do with desire

00:10:34.840 --> 00:10:36.460 align:middle line:90%
and a number of other things.

00:10:36.460 --> 00:10:38.290 align:middle line:84%
It's also societally
conditioned,

00:10:38.290 --> 00:10:40.070 align:middle line:84%
driven by the
subconscious, right?

00:10:40.070 --> 00:10:40.420 align:middle line:90%
>>L'ESPERANCE: Very much so.

00:10:40.420 --> 00:10:42.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So those
kinds of desires

00:10:42.070 --> 00:10:44.950 align:middle line:84%
may not be in alignment
with what this has in mind.

00:10:44.950 --> 00:10:46.360 align:middle line:84%
And one thing you
say in the book

00:10:46.360 --> 00:10:51.070 align:middle line:84%
is, it's kind of surprising
that so few people genuinely

00:10:51.070 --> 00:10:53.330 align:middle line:90%
choose to take this journey.

00:10:53.330 --> 00:10:56.411 align:middle line:84%
And I find this
surprising as well.

00:10:56.411 --> 00:10:57.910 align:middle line:84%
>>L'ESPERANCE: Well
like I mentioned

00:10:57.910 --> 00:11:00.700 align:middle line:84%
before, I thought everybody
else was just like me.

00:11:00.700 --> 00:11:03.430 align:middle line:84%
And it took a long time
for me to understand

00:11:03.430 --> 00:11:06.370 align:middle line:90%
that this wasn't the case.

00:11:06.370 --> 00:11:09.040 align:middle line:84%
And it's probably the
reason that the world

00:11:09.040 --> 00:11:11.980 align:middle line:84%
is standing at this threshold
